        "`startupFailFastServiceTimeout` is fixed at 250ms before startup continues",
        "`startupBackgroundServices.health` returns immediately on default when no immediate error is present, so delayed failures are not consistently propagated",
        "The startup contract therefore allows startup success despite fail-fast services that fail just after the startup gate"
      ],
      "suggestion": "Treat fail-fast startup supervision as a stable startup barrier: either await each fail-fast service's first terminal error with a bounded startup context, or require each fail-fast service to send periodic health/error status that startup health checks poll for a grace window before continuing, with a dedicated timeout and explicit failure return path.",
